

We need a permanent, comprehensive ICD-10 code suggestion system for Indian hospital insurance pre-authorization. The current system has gaps — valid conditions like Eclampsia, Pericarditis, and Perforated Appendicitis are incorrectly falling back to R69 (unspecified illness).

**Goal:** Build a 3-tier ICD database that covers 99.9% of hospital admissions, with R69 only used for truly undiagnosed or test cases.

---

## ARCHITECTURE

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  TIER 1: ENRICHED DATABASE (300+ conditions)                               │
│  Complete metadata: Hindi terms, costs, LOS, TPA triggers, admission       │
│  criteria, clinical markers, PMJAY codes, documentation requirements       │
│  → Used for: Full pre-auth document generation with clinical intelligence  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                                    ↓ If not found
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  TIER 2: EXTENDED LOOKUP (2000+ conditions)                                │
│  Basic metadata: Code, Description, Search terms (English + Hindi),        │
│  Specialty, Surgical flag, Typical LOS                                     │
│  → Used for: Valid ICD assignment when full metadata not available         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                                    ↓ If not found
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  TIER 3: COMPLETE ICD-10-CM REFERENCE (15,000+ codes)                      │
│  Minimal: Code + Official Description                                       │
│  → Used for: Rare but valid conditions, safety net                         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                                    ↓ If STILL not found
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  FLOOR: R69 (Illness, unspecified)                                         │
│  → Used for: Test data, gibberish, truly undiagnosed only                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

